{
  "text": "1) The microstructures are contained in primary cherts without any evidence of metasomatic replacement (silicification) of precursory non-siliceous sediments. The matrix, in which the microfossils are embedded, is rich in cloudy carbonaceous particles, and locally forms lamination [CITATION_1] . Rare-earth elements and Y data suggest that the microfossil-bearing black cherts were precipitated from water masses of seawater compositions, with some input of continental run-off and/or low temperature hydrothermal fluids [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "53592928",
